    <name>periscope</name>
    <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
    <summary>Live observability + time-travel debugger for PHP (engine-level).</summary>
    <description>
        php-periscope is a Zend Observer API extension that records every
        userland function call, captured arguments, return values, SQL,
        log lines, cache ops, jobs, events, exceptions and outbound HTTP
        into a compact Cap'n Proto trace file. Pair with the
        periscope-daemon (Rust) and the SolidJS UI to scrub through any
        request and inspect what the code was doing at any moment.

        v1 is Laravel-only on the framework side (via the
        thamibn/php-periscope-laravel Composer adapter), but this extension is
        framework-agnostic: any PHP 8.3 SAPI is supported.

        Build requirements: Cap'n Proto C++ library
        (brew install capnp / apt-get install libcapnp-dev) plus a C++17
        toolchain.
    </description>

    <lead>
        <name>Thamsanca Ntuli</name>
        <user>thamibn</user>
        <email>thamibn@gmail.com</email>
        <active>yes</active>
    </lead>

